    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A high quality zinc oxide pigment prepared by the French process, which is an indirect technique that vaporizes metallic zinc; the vapors react with air and precipitate as pure zinc oxide. Most commercial zinc oxide pigments are made by this method.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種質佳的氧化鋅顏料，以法國法（French process）製成。法國方法採間接方法製作，先蒸發鋅金屬，再讓蒸氣與空氣起反應，沉澱成純氧化鋅。市面上大部分的氧化鋅顏料都以此法製造。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een hoogwaardig pigment van zinkoxide dat wordt gemaakt volgens het Franse procedé, een indirecte techniek om metallisch zink te verdampen. De dampen reageren met de lucht en precipiteren als zuivere zinkoxide. De meeste commerciële pigmenten uit zinkoxide worden op deze manier gemaakt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
